The paper deals with editing face images using a visual representation that includes geometry, face segmentation, albedo, illumination, and detail map. This involves computer vision techniques such as morphable face models, image decomposition, and shading. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves graphics techniques such as relighting and makeup transfer, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics). Additionally, the paper evaluates its method using user studies and online attractiveness evaluation, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as non-parametric modifications, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves multimedia techniques such as image editing, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
